Building an AI system for intelligent querying and compliance analysis of US MNO device requirement specifications.

**Why:** Pure RAG failed because it can't handle cross-document dependencies, hierarchical requirement structure, or standards layering inherent in telecom requirement docs.

**Agreed architecture:** Knowledge Graph + RAG hybrid
- Graph scoping identifies WHERE to look (cross-doc traversal)
- Targeted vector RAG ranks WHAT's most relevant within that scope
- Hierarchy provides structural CONTEXT for LLM synthesis
- Standards specs ingested selectively (Option C — only referenced sections + surrounding context)
- Feature taxonomy derived bottom-up from documents (LLM + human review)
- Relationship types between VZW reqs and 3GPP: DEFER / CONSTRAIN / OVERRIDE / EXTEND

**Constraints:**
- PoC uses Claude/Gemini on publicly available VZW OA docs (5 PDFs in repo)
- Production uses proprietary LLM (context TBD, supports thinking mode), on-premise, no external LLMs
- Some flexibility for open-source on-premise models

**Current status (2026-04-11):** Technical Design Document written (`TDD_Telecom_Requirements_AI_System.md`). Next step is PoC implementation starting with PDF extraction.

**How to apply:** All design decisions should respect the on-premise/proprietary LLM constraint. Avoid Claude/Gemini-specific features. Architecture must scale from 5 docs to GBs of docs across MNOs.
